<html>
	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 96/10-Living Proof</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6001.html?worth+PCFN18.gif+Front%20Page>
<img src="/ads/PCFN18.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/10-Living Proof</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						Arthur Durone, 32, an underwater-demolition specialist from San Gabriel, was riding his bike five years ago when he was hit by an uninsured motorist. He flew over the top of the car as it sped off. The driver was not charged with leaving the scene because, as it happened, Mr. Durone's hand had caught in her luggage rack. He was dragged four-tenths of a mile until the car's engine -- damaged by the impact -- conked out. Amazingly, he lived.<p>
Under today's auto-insurance system, he got nothing beyond the uninsured-motorist coverage he had purchased. He lost all his savings and his house. Under Prop 200, he would have had all his medical and rehab covered, plus $30,000 a year of lost wages, up to a combined limit of $1 million, plus up to $250,000 more for pain and suffering. All that for less than the cost of auto insurance today. 
When you come right down to it, Prop 200 wasn't a fight between people like me and Ralph. It was between ordinary people like Arthur Durone and Jeff Reuvekamp (see "<A href="/articles/Z9610C06.html">Could It Be the Money?</A>").<p>

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
</td><td width=150 valign=top>

<center>
		
	<a href="/index.html">
	<IMG SRC="/imgs/datalineyellow.gif" border=0 alt="Worth"></a><p>
</center>
<pre>


</pre>
					<tt><font size=+1>
					<center>
						<img src="/imgs/1page.gif"><br>About 1 page

					</font>
					</tt>
					</center>

					<pre>
					</pre>


					</font>
					<p>

					<p>

					<p>
	
		
</td>
	</tr>
	<tr><td width=390>
	
		<center>
		<p>
