	<head>
		<title> Worth OnLine - 96/11-Tellers on the Telly</title>
	</head>
	
	<body background="/imgs/goldbarsmooth.gif" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"
	      text="#000000" link="#FF0000" vlink="#BB0000"> 	
	<a name="#top">
	<table width=550 cellpadding=10 cellspacing=5>
	
	<tr>
		<td width=390 valign=top> 
		
		<a href=/cgi/ad-relay.cgi?http://www.pcfn.com/6001.html?worth+PCFN18.gif+Front%20Page>
<img src="/ads/PCFN18.gif" border=3 width=372 height=45 alt="PC Financial Network"></a>


		</td>
		<td  width=150>
		<!-- empty cell -->
		</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	<td width=390 valign=top>
		
		<center>
		<p>
		<b><a href="/index.html">Home</a>  |  <a href="/departments/departments.html">Departments</a>  |  <a href="/search/query.html">Search</a>  |  <a href="/forums/index.html">Message Boards</a></b>
		<pre>
		</pre>
				<font size=5><b></b></font><br>
				<font size=6><b>96/11-Tellers on the Telly</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						Hey, my six-month CD just got its own show!<p>
By Elizabeth Macdonald<p>
Here's one way to get your kids to stop watching Pinky and the Brain -- call up your dull old checking account on TV. <p>
This fall <a name="NYSE:BBI"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=10183"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Barnett Bank</b></a> in Orlando, Florida, will let its customers do just that, through its new TV banking service. Customers must subscribe to Time Warner's interactive cable network, a pilot project that lets viewers get movies and pizzas delivered to their doorstep. Consumers click their remote controls, enter a PIN, and direct cartoon tellers to pay bills, transfer money between accounts, or check ATM withdrawals.<p>
Sounds smart -- home banking has been notoriously expensive, with consumers shelling out hundreds of dollars for PCs and modems to get services that are free in bank branches. Less than 1 percent of U.S. households became PC bankers in the first 15 years of home banking; maybe paying credit-card bills during commercials will be an easier sell.<p>
KEYWORDS:online banking, television banking

					</font>
					<p>
		
		
		
