				<font size=6><b>96/06-Investing Briefs</b></font><br>
				<font size=4></font><p>
				</center>
				
				<blockquote>
					<center>
						<font size=4><b><i></i></b></font><p>
					</center>
					<font size=4>
						Hoover's Horsemen Company-information service Hoover's Online has unveiled a new area on its Web site (www.hoovers.com), with information on pending initial public offerings and updates after they go to market. Now showing: "The Four Horsemen Special Report," which provides profiles and prospectuses of four companies that have built search software for the World Wide Web. Although two of the companies, <a name="NASD:LCOS"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=48044"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Lycos</b></a> and <a name="NASD:YHOO"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=48043"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Yahoo!</b></a>, are already out of the gate, investors can get an early peek at Excite and InfoSeek via the Net, <a name="NASD:AMER"></a><b>America Online</b>, and <a name="NASD:MSFT"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=14120"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Microsoft</b></a> Network (keyword: Hoovers).<p>Rating Big Brokers
A 16-page survey from the National Council of Individual Investors rates the ten largest securities brokers. In the rankings -- based on charges for trading 500 shares of a $10 stock, breadth of services, and 1995 securities recommendations and disciplinary records -- A. G. Edwards & Sons finished first and Prudential Securities last. 
The survey is available for five dollars from NCII (800-663-8516), a ten-month-old nonprofit group in Washington, D.C., that says it seeks "to create a level playing field between powerful industry forces and small investors."<p>FINANCIAL FOOTNOTES
<a name="NASD:INTU"></a><a href="http://www.hoovers.com/cgi-bin/brand_worth_mlist.cgi?mode=full&index_code=16001"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>Intuit</b></a>'s Investor Insight (800-624-8742), originally part of Quicken Deluxe 5, is now available as a stand-alone program offering stock news, analysts' ratings, company research, and simple graphs ($9.95 a month for 10 securities or $19.95 for 50).... <a name="FUND:PRSUX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/PRSUX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>T. Rowe Price Small-Cap Value Fund</b></a>, rated $$$$$ by Worth, has closed to new investors.... Berger Associates has started the <a name="FUND:BENGX"></a><a href="http://www.investools.com/cgi-bin/Library/t_page.pl/worth/BENGX"><img src="/imgs/graph.gif" border=0><b>New Generation Fund</b></a> (800-333-1001), which will invest in companies of any size or sector, 
anywhere in the world.... People can choose among eight style-diversified strategies to invest in 11 funds created by consultant Frank Russell Co. in Tacoma, Washington, and available through A. G. Edwards's brokers.<p><p><p>
